text: Some of it is genuine rubbish that has been picked up off the beach by local people, but the majority has been illegally dumped household waste.

Not against having street bins, where it makes sense to, but a lot of the bins around Dublin are nice to haves more so than a necessity. I think addressing the root cause as to why people feel it necessary to use street bins for household waste is better long term solution.
